Smart To-Do List App
A modern, feature-rich task management application built with React and Firebase. Organize your life efficiently with smart categorization, priority management, and intelligent reminders.

âœ¨ Features
ğŸ” Authentication

Email/Password Authentication: Secure account creation and login
Google OAuth Integration: One-click sign-in with Google
Persistent Sessions: Stay logged in across browser sessions

ğŸ“ Task Management

Smart Categorization: Organize tasks by Work, Personal, School, Health, Shopping
Priority Levels: Mark tasks as Low, Medium, or High priority
Due Date & Time: Set specific deadlines for better time management
Rich Descriptions: Add detailed notes to your tasks

ğŸ”” Smart Notifications

Configurable Reminders: Set alerts from 5 minutes to 1 day before due time
Browser Notifications: Native desktop notifications for timely reminders
Overdue Tracking: Visual indicators for past-due tasks

ğŸ¯ Advanced Filtering

Category Filtering: View tasks by specific categories
Status Filtering: Filter by pending, completed, or high priority
Due Date Filtering: See tasks due today or overdue items
Real-time Search: Instant task filtering and organization

ğŸ“Š Progress Tracking

Visual Progress Bar: See completion percentage at a glance
Task Statistics: Track total, completed, and pending tasks
Category Breakdown: Monitor progress across different life areas

ğŸ¨ Modern UI/UX

Responsive Design: Seamless experience on desktop, tablet, and mobile
Smooth Animations: Delightful micro-interactions and transitions
Clean Interface: Minimalist design focused on productivity
Dark Mode Ready: Beautiful gradient themes

ğŸš€ Quick Start
Prerequisites

Node.js (v14 or higher)
npm or yarn
Firebase account

Installation

Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/yourusername/smart-todo-app.git
cd smart-todo-app

Install dependencies
bashnpm install

Firebase Setup

Create a new Firebase project at Firebase Console
Enable Authentication (Email/Password and Google providers)
Create a Firestore database
Copy your Firebase config to src/firebase/config.js


Start the development server
bashnpm start

Open your browser
Navigate to http://localhost:3000

ğŸ”§ Configuration
Firebase Configuration
Update src/firebase/config.js with your Firebase project credentials:
javascriptconst firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "your-api-key",
  authDomain: "your-project.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId: "your-project-id",
  storageBucket: "your-project.firebasestorage.app",
  messagingSenderId: "your-sender-id",
  appId: "your-app-id"
};
Firestore Security Rules
Add these rules to your Firestore database:
javascriptrules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /tasks/{document} {
      allow read, write, update, delete: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;
      allow create: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.userId;
    }
  }
}
ğŸ“± Usage
Getting Started

Sign Up: Create an account or sign in with Google
Add Your First Task: Click "Add Task" to create your first to-do item
Organize: Choose categories and set priorities for better organization
Set Reminders: Enable notifications for important deadlines
Track Progress: Monitor your productivity with built-in analytics

Task Management

Create: Click the "+" button or "Add Task" to create new tasks
Edit: Click the edit icon on any task to modify details
Complete: Check the circle next to tasks to mark them done
Delete: Use the trash icon to remove tasks permanently

Categories & Filtering

Use the sidebar to filter tasks by category or status
Switch between "All Tasks", "Pending", "Completed", and "High Priority"
View progress statistics in the Quick Stats panel

